'''Linnévatnet''' is a lake in [[Nordenskiöld Land]] at [[Spitsbergen]], [[Svalbard]]. It is located in the lower part of the valley [[Linnédalen]], and has a length of about 4.5 kilometers. The lake is among the largest lakes of Spitsbergen. It is named after Swedish botanist [[Carl Linnaeus]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Linnévatnet |title=Linnévatnet (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Arctic Pilot: Sailing directions Svalbard&ndash;Jan Mayen |year=1988 | volume =7 |publisher=The Norwegian Hydrographic Service and The Norwegian Polar Institute |location=Stavanger |language= |isbn=82-90653-06-9 |page=220}}</ref>

